The paper deals with the problem of topology discovery in wireless networks, which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The use of user reports and crowd sourcing is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which could place it in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
